---
import { BaseLayout } from "@walle/layouts";
---

<BaseLayout
  headerTitle="Privacy Policy"
  headerDescription="Privacy Policy describing data collection and processing practices."
  headerRobots="noindex, nofollow"
>
  <section class="container prose">
    <h1 style="padding-top: 2rem;">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: Jun 19, 2026</p>
    <p>
      This notice describes how Fabrizio Cafolla (<a
        href="https://fabriziocafolla.com/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">fabriziocafolla.com</a
      >) processes users’ personal data. The site does not use any analytics or tracking tools. The
      only processing of personal data concerns the optional newsletter subscription.
    </p>

    <h4>1. Data Controller</h4>
    <p>
      The data controller is Fabrizio Cafolla, owner of this blog. For any privacy-related requests,
      you can contact me via LinkedIn.
    </p>

    <h4>2. Data Collected</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Browsing data:</strong> No analytics, profiling, or tracking data is collected from users
        visiting the site. The site does not use third-party analytics tools.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Newsletter data:</strong> If you subscribe to the newsletter, the email address you provide
        is collected for the sole purpose of sending communications about new articles.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Purpose and Legal Basis of Processing</h4>
    <h5>3.1 Newsletter</h5>
    <p>
      Processing of newsletter subscription data is based on your explicit consent pursuant to Art.
      6(1)(a) GDPR and Art. 130 of Italian Legislative Decree 196/2003 (Privacy Code).
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sending newsletter communications about new articles published on the blog</li>
      <li>Managing subscription and unsubscription requests</li>
      <li>Compliance with legal obligations related to electronic communications</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>4. Cookies</h4>
    <p>
      The site does not use analytics, profiling, or marketing cookies. Only strictly necessary
      technical cookies may be used to ensure the site functions correctly.
    </p>

    <h4>5. Data Processing and Third Parties</h4>

    <h5>5.1 Newsletter - Brevo</h5>
    <p>
      Newsletter subscription data is processed through Brevo (formerly Sendinblue), a marketing
      automation platform. By subscribing to the newsletter, you agree that your personal
      information will be transferred to Brevo for processing in accordance with <a
        href="https://www.brevo.com/legal/privacypolicy/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener">Brevo's Privacy Policy</a
      >. Brevo acts as a data processor and processes data exclusively on our behalf and according
      to our instructions. Data transfer to Brevo is based on adequate safeguards as required by
      GDPR.
    </p>

    <h4>6. Users' Rights</h4>
    <p>
      Regarding newsletter subscription data, you can unsubscribe at any time using the link in
      emails or contacting us directly. You may also request access, rectification, or deletion of
      your data.
    </p>
    <p>
      To exercise these rights, contact me using the contact details available on the site. You also
      have the right to lodge a complaint with the Italian Data Protection Authority (Garante per la
      protezione dei dati personali).
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
